title: Paw discography (7 discs, includes rarities)
description:
Paw are an alternative rock band from Kansas, who became moderately popular in the grunge era


They are best known for their song Jessie, which was featured on the soundtrack of the 1995 version of Road Rash (along with an altered version of the music video)


The band split up sometime in the late 90s, only ever releasing two albums, reforming in 2000 with a new drummer and bassist, they released an EP, and split up again...now they have reunited again, hopefully they will go on a tour or release some new material or something


Anyway, seeing as that&#039;s about as much as I know about the band, let&#039;s get to the stuff you want to hear


This torrent includes:


Albums:
Dragline (1993)
Death to Traitors (1995)

Rarities compilation:
Keep The Last Bullet For Yourself (1998)

Live bootleg:
Live at the Bottleneck (2000)

Demos:
Death to Traitors sessions (early 1995?)


The files are MP3, I&#039;m not entirely sure what bitrate, I downloaded these from some obscure South American MP3 blog


Enjoy
